My friends and I (a group of 6) stopped by Casa Margarita to get a quick bite during the Chicago Pride events. When we were seated the waitress informed us that she would need to hold one of our ID's because they get a large number of walkouts. We obliged. From that moment on the service was poor. We barely got checked on. Through out the hour we were there we were seen by multiple servers and ours was no where to be found. It was busy so we had a wait for our food. We understood that and did not complain. When we got our food each person was not satisfied with their meal. The food was rather lackluster. After we all had finished our meals it took 10-15 minutes for us to get the check (by the way they do not split checks so we all had to split one check). The servers were taking too long to come back so one of my friends had to get up and take our money into the restaurant so that we could pay, retrieve our friend's ID, and leave. It had been expressed to my friend that the waitress only asked for the ID's of the two tables with Black people in our area. The White people in our area were not required to hand over an ID. So we were racially profiled, the food sucked, and the service was trash. Save your time and money and eat somewhere else.

After picking out coupons for restaurants we have not been to yet,  we landed on casa margarita. It was a short walk considering where we were walking from but there is plenty of parking all around this location.  We were taken to a seat quickly but they were not busy.  The restaurant is small and kind of dark and has no windows but plenty of tv's on the wall. The menu is a little pricey compared to others locally but could be because of its location close to navy pier. We were brought hot tortilla chips and a warm salsa that was quite tasty.  We decided on the margarita flight which gives you 5 8oz margaritas. They were brought out in a nice carrier/holder.  The margaritas were very well made and I could see myself enjoying these more frequently.  We ordered the ceviche which was dryer than what I am used to and did lack some heat and saltiness.  It was still ok but I will probably not order it again. We decided to order the combo fajitas which gives you shrimp,  steak and chicken.  The fajitas were not bad but the steak appeared a bit tough to chew.  The shrimp still had the tail on so make sure you pull tails off first.  I am more accustomed to seeing the tails removed for fajitas but it's their choice.  Warm tortillas and fajitas were definitely filling.  We decided to order the fried ice cream as well. This took quite some time to get but was worth the wait.  I suggest you order dessert before you are done to give them adequate time.  All in all the meal was worth going and we will be back.  Total time at restaurant was 2 hours so make sure you have time.  Some times good food can't be rushed.  I recommend this restaurant to all locals and those visiting who wish so good Mexican food.
